dabd62a4-5954-4b92-b704-132cec531cab.1a75cf88-d996-49b0-88c3-419982463d58.transition.description=failure dabd62a4-5954-4b92-b704-132cec531cab.b6ec5dbe-8b07-457a-9800-02092e5311df.description=This operation runs a SQL command. Inputs\: DBServerName - The hostname or ip address of the database server. DbType - The type of database to connect to. Valid values\: Oracle, MSSQL, Sybase, Netcool, DB2, PostgreSQL and Custom. Default value\: Oracle Username - The username to use when connecting to the database. Password - The password to use when connecting to the database. instance - The name instance (for MSSQL Server). Leave it blank for default instance. DbPort - The port to connect to. Default values\: Oracle\: 1521, MSSQL\: 1433, Sybase\: 5000, Netcool\: 4100, DB2\: 50000, PostgreSQL\: 5432. Database - The name of the database. authenticationType - The type of authentication used to access the database (applicable only to MSSQL type). Valid values\: sql, windows (for MSSQL) Default value\: sql dbClass - The classname of the JDBC driver to use. dbURL - The url required to load up the driver and make your connection. Command - The command to execute. timeout - Seconds to wait before timing out the SQL command execution. When the default value is used, there is no limit on the amount of time allowed for a running command to complete. Default value\: 0 databasePoolingProperties - Properties for database pooling configuration. This parameter replaces the databasePooling.properties file from 9x version (you may copy-paste the file content here). Pooling is disabled by default. For more details check the /Library/Operations/Database/JDBC folder description. Example\: db.pooling.enable\=true resultSetType - the result set type. See JDBC folder description for more details. Valid values\: TYPE_FORWARD_ONLY, TYPE_SCROLL_INSENSITIVE,TYPE_SCROLL_SENSITIVE. Default value\: TYPE_FORWARD_ONLY resultSetConcurrency - the result set concurrency. See JDBC folder description for more details. Valid values\: CONCUR_READ_ONLY, CONCUR_UPDATABLE Default value\: CONCUR_READ_ONLY Results\: returnResult - This is the primary output. It contains the "Command completed successfully" message if the operation succeeded, or a failure message otherwise. outputText - The return result of SQL command. updateCount - The update count of the command executed. Responses\: success - The command was executed successfully. failure - Failed to execute the command. Note\: 1. Check the JDBC folder description for details on how to load database connectors. 2. In case of using subprograms like (GET_LINE, GET_LINES, NEW_LINE, PUT, PUT_LUNE) from DBMS_OUTPUT package, the DBMS_OUTPUT.ENABLE() declaration should be used before of these calls. 3. Use the 'Command' input with caution as it can expose the target system to security risks. By exposing the 'Command' input as a prompt to the user, it will enable the user to execute any SQL command on the target system taking into account the permissions of the credentials given as inputs. dabd62a4-5954-4b92-b704-132cec531cab.cf53b024-51c9-417d-8387-7a360313c9a4.description=
This operation does not do anything. It can be used to filter flow variables by defining them as inputs and filtering them in the Results tab.

Inputs\:
    field1 – An optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.
    field2 – An optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.
    field3 – An optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.
    field4 – An optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.

Results\:
    returnResult - This is the primary output. It contains the value of  "field1" as it was specified at input or when filtered. 

Responses\:
    success - The operation completed as stated in the description.
dabd62a4-5954-4b92-b704-132cec531cab.description=
This Flow is used to update table records in SLS Database.

Inputs\:

	SLS_CUSTOMERZNUMBER	\:	Customer Z Number from  loan details
	SLS_DIVISION	\:	Division
	SLS_STATE		\:	state
	SLS_DocType	\:	Application type 
	SLS_PROCESS_GROUP	\:	Process group
	SLS_OPERATOR	\:	operator
	SLS_STATUS		\:	status
	SLS_PRIORITY	\:	priority level
	SLS_LOCATION	\:	location
	SLS_ACTION_BY	\:	action by date
	SLS_COMMENTS	\:	any comments
	SLS_BSB		\:	BSB
	SLS_MANAGER_NO	\:	Manager no
	SLS_REGION_NO	\:	Region Number
	SLS_NUMBER_REWORKS	\:	Rework Number

output\:
	RESULT\:	Command was executed successfully


Responses\:
    success - The command was executed successfully.
    failure - Failed to execute the command.



Note\:
1. please enter the input commad in the below format.
Exec SLA_SSCIndex_Upd @CustomerID\=${SLS_CUSTOMERZNUMBER}, @Division\=${SLS_DIVISION}, @SSC\=${SLS_STATE},  @Doctype\='${SLS_DocType}' , @ProcessGroup \=${SLS_PROCESS_GROUP}, @OperatorID\=${SLS_OPERATOR}, @Status\=${SLS_STATUS}, @Priority\= ${SLS_PRIORITY}, @Location\=${SLS_LOCATION}, @ActionBy\= '${SLS_ACTION_BY}', @Comments\='${SLS_COMMENTS}', @BSBNumb\=${SLS_BSB}, @ManagerNumb\=${SLS_MANAGER_NO}, @RegionNumb\='${SLS_REGION_NO}', @NumbReworks\=${SLS_NUMBER_REWORKS}
flow.name: Insert Record in SLS DB
